riter%20David%20Koepp%2C%20follows%20Scarlett%20Johansson%20as%20the%20leader%20of%20a%20team%20of%20operatives%20who%20travel%20to%20an%20island%20research%20facility%20to%20take%20genetic%20material%20from%20dinosaurs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Edwards%2C%20making%20the%20movie%20checked%20off%20a%20childhood%20dream%20of%20working%20alongside%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsteven-spielberg-movies-ranked-from-worst-to-best%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESteven%20Spielberg%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20was%20heavily%20involved%20in%20the%20filmmaking%20process.%20And%20it%20shows%20as%20%26quot%3BRebirth%26quot%3B%20features%20several%20hat%20tips%20to%20the%20master%2C%20ranging%20from%20%26quot%3BJurassic%20Park%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3BJaws.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20hate%20the%20word%20IP%2C%20but%20there%20are%20only%20two%20franchises%20I%20would%20absolutely%20drop%20everything%20for%20and%20just%20do%20them.%20I%20already%20did%20one%20of%20them%20with%20'Star%20Wars%2C'%20and%20this%20was%20the%20other%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20Edwards%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BSo%20when%20Steven%20gives%20you%20this%20script%2C%20you're%20just%20checkmated%20immediately.%20The%20idea%20that%20you%20turn%20Steven%20Spielberg%20down%20is%20impossible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20spoke%20with%20Edwards%20while%20he%20was%20in%20New%20York%20City%20about%20the%20hourslong%20conversations%20he%20had%20with%20Spielberg%20while%20making%20the%20movie%2C%20his%20thoughts%20on%20%26quot%3BRogue%20One%26quot%3B%20as%20it%20nears%20its%2010th%20anniversary%2C%20and%20whether%20he'd%20ever%20consider%20making%20another%20%26quot%3BStar%20Wars%26quot%3B%20movie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gareth%20Edwards%20in%20a%20grey%20suit%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68653fcff748d8c055f4ce74%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224012%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BJurassic%20World%20Rebirth%26quot%3B%20director%20Gareth%20Edwards.%3Cp%3EJohn%20Nacion%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBusiness%20Insider%3A%20So%20what%20led%20you%20to%20sign%20onto%20%26quot%3BJurassic%26quot%3B%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20%26quot%3BThe%20Creator%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20started%20the%20process%20of%20what%20am%20I%20going%20to%20do%20next.%20There%20was%20a%20thing%20in%20my%20mind%20that%20I%20was%20excited%20about.%20And%20in%20that%20process%2C%20a%20sequence%20from%20%26quot%3BJurassic%20Park%26quot%3B%20entered%20my%20mind%2C%20and%20I%20forgot%20how%20they%20pulled%20it%20off%2C%20so%20I%20just%20put%20it%20on%20to%20get%20a%20refresher.%20I'm%20doing%20this%20with%20%26quot%3BJurassic%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20next%20day%20my%20friend%20saw%20on%20the%20internet%20that%20Universal%20was%20looking%20for%20a%20director%20for%20a%20new%20%26quot%3BJurassic%26quot%3B%20movie.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20sent%20that%20to%20my%20agent%2C%20and%20I%20just%20typed%20in%20the%20text%20with%20the%20link%20to%20the%20story%2C%20%26quot%3BIs%20this%20stupid%3F%26quot%3B%20hoping%20he'd%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BYes%2C%20stay%20away.%26quot%3B%20And%20hours%20later%2C%20my%20agent%20got%20back%20to%20me%2C%20and%20the%20ball%20started%20rolling.%20Be%20careful%20what%20you%20wish%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20I%20really%20enjoyed%20about%20%26quot%3BRebirth%26quot%3B%20is%20its%20stand-alone%20feel.%20Was%20that%20intentional%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20in%20David%20Koepp's%20script.%20That's%20why%20I%20really%20liked%20it.%20What%20the%20best%20sequels%20have%20in%20common%20is%20that%20the%20first%20one%20didn't%20know%20it%20was%20part%20of%20a%20trilogy%20or%20the%20start%20of%20sequels.%20It%20was%20just%20this%20self-contained%20story.%20So%20that's%20the%20way%20to%20go%2C%20to%20try%20to%20tell%20the%20best%20film%20you%20can.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20then%20a%20high-class%20problem%20after%20that.%20And%20I'm%20not%20joking%2C%20but%20I%20haven't%20had%20a%20single%20conversation%20about%20a%20sequel%20with%20anyone%20from%20Universal%20or%20the%20producers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThat%20was%20my%20follow-up.%20Nobody%20tapped%20you%20on%20the%20shoulder%20and%20suggested%20a%20more%20heavy-handed%20way%20to%20tease%20another%20movie%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo.%20It%20was%20even%20a%20joke%20with%20the%20actors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222220%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22jurassic%20park%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f104bcd4dca68396f2342a4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221296%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BJurassic%20Park.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EUniversal%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20the%20movie%20also%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20nostalgia%2C%20with%20hat%20tips%20ranging%20from%20%26quot%3BJurassic%20Park%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3BJaws.%20%26quot%3B%20Did%20that%20come%20organically%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20got%20the%20script%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20a%20magical%20ticket%20back%20to%20being%20a%20kid%20again.%20So%20a%20lot%20of%20that%20was%20already%20in%20there%2C%20and%20half%20of%20it%20I%20probably%20brought%20with%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20mean%2C%20you're%20making%20a%20movie%20for%20Amblin%20that%20features%20a%20giant%20creature%20in%20the%20water.%20Of%20course%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20lean%20into%20%26quot%3BJaws.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYeah.%20The%20script%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThey're%20chasing%20a%20giant%20dinosaur%20in%20the%20water%2C%20on%20a%20boat%2C%20with%20a%20rifle%20leading%20out%20the%20front%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20you're%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BGuys%2C%20I%20don't%20know%20if%20you've%20ever%20seen%20this%20movie%20called%20'Jaws%2C'%20but%20I%20don't%20know%20how%20we%20escape%20those%20visuals.%26quot%3B%20So%20it%20was%20a%20difficult%20situation%2C%20and%20the%20only%20way%20I%20got%20through%20it%20was%20this%20being%20a%20giant%20love%20letter%20to%20Steven%20Spielberg.%20Whenever%20there's%20a%20gap%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20put%20something%20in%20that%20is%20a%20reflection%20of%20something%20from%20his%20movies%20that%20we%20love.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20have%20now%20worked%20with%20two%20faces%20on%20the%20Mt.%20Rushmore%20of%20American%20cinema%2C%20George%20Lucas%20and%20Steven%20Spielberg.%20Compare%20and%20contrast%20working%20for%20them.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20George%20had%20retired%20when%20we%20started%20%26quot%3BRogue%20One%2C%26quot%3B%20so%20he%20was%20totally%20happy%20for%20us%20to%20go%20do%20our%20thing.%20But%20I%20did%20have%20the%20more%20surreal%20moment%20of%20showing%20him%20around%20the%20set%20of%20%26quot%3BRogue%20One.%26quot%3B%20But%20what%20I%20did%20to%20take%20the%20pressure%20off%20myself%2C%20seeing%20I%20was%20doing%20a%20%26quot%3BStar%20Wars%26quot%3B%20spin-off%2C%20I%20was%20competing%20with%20the%20likes%20of%20the%20holiday%20special%20and%20Caravan%20of%20Courage%2C%20the%20Ewok%20adventure.%20So%20I%20jokingly%20framed%20those%20movie%20posters%20in%20my%20office%20as%20a%20reminder%20to%20me%20that%20I%20just%20have%20to%20do%20better%20than%20those.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20one%20day%20I%20was%20told%20George%20is%20here%2C%20and%20he%20just%20walked%20into%20the%20office%2C%20and%20I%20was%20blown%20away.%20And%20as%20I%20was%20talking%20to%20him%2C%20I%20realized%20the%20posters%20on%20the%20wall.%20So%20I'm%20trying%20to%20be%20as%20animated%20as%20possible%20so%20he%20wouldn't%20look%20at%20the%20wall.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteven%20developed%20the%20story%20with%20David%2C%20so%20he%20was%20fully%20engaged%20from%20the%20start.%20He%20was%20in%20the%20meetings%20during%20preproduction.%20He%20would%20call%20me%20when%20I%20started%20shooting.%20He%20watched%20the%20dallies%20every%20day.%20We%20even%20se