ng%20the%20most%20of%20your%20press-on%20nails.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c739f9ce-d0a5-43c8-9530-262925f87e1e%5C%22%3EFile%20down%20the%20press-on%20nail%20to%20get%20a%20better%20fit%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223745%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Close-up%20of%20purple%20nails%2C%20as%20the%20right%20hand%20holding%20a%20nail%20file%20shapes%20the%20thumbnail%20of%20the%20left%20hand.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F685d9ee4f748d8c055f473d0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222809%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFiling%20the%20press-on%20nails%20can%20help%20improve%20the%20fit.%3Cp%3EIryna%20Marienko%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Julie%20Kandalec%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-diary-mobile-celebrity-manicurist-for-nearly-50-years-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecelebrity%20manicurist%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20founder%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.julieknailacademy.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJulie%20K%20Nail%20Academy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20most%20important%20aspect%20of%20making%20press-on%20nails%20last%20is%20making%20sure%20each%20one%20fits%20properly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20trying%20on%20each%20press-on%2C%20she%20said%20to%20take%20note%20of%20how%20it%20fits%20along%20the%20sides%20and%20natural%20curve%20of%20your%20nail.%20For%20example%2C%20she%20told%20BI%20that%20applying%20a%20curved%20press-on%20onto%20a%20flatter%20natural%20nail%20will%20likely%20cause%20it%20to%20pop%20up%20because%20of%20the%20poor%20fit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20tiniest%20bit%20of%20pressure%20is%20usually%20OK.%20But%20if%20you%20really%20have%20to%20press%20it%20on%20there%2C%20it's%20gonna%20last%20a%20day%2C%20and%20it's%20popping%20off.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20particularly%20flat%20nail%20beds%20and%20your%20press-ons%20are%20curved%2C%20Kandalec%20said%20to%20size%20up%20on%20the%20nail%20for%20a%20bigger%2C%20flatter%20well.%20Then%2C%20file%20down%20the%20sides%20to%20accommodate%20the%20size%20of%20your%20natural%20nail.%20If%20you%20can%20feel%20the%20sides%20against%20your%20nail%20bed%2C%20it's%20too%20big.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229336f5bc-c428-4534-8216-a20543198a1c%5C%22%3EUse%20a%20file%20on%20the%20surface%20of%20your%20natural%20nail%20and%20the%20underside%20of%20the%20press-on%20nail%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKandalec%20recommends%20using%20a%20file%20on%20both%20your%20natural%20nail%20and%20the%20underside%20of%20the%20press-on%20nail%20to%20ensure%20maximum%20grip%20for%20the%20glue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20to%20flick%20the%20file%20inside%20the%20press-on%20nail%20in%20a%20few%20different%20directions%20to%20create%20some%20roughness%20for%20better%20adhesion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20use%20a%20file%20on%20the%20top%20surface%20of%20your%20natural%20nail%20to%20remove%20any%20excess%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrying-japanese-gel-manicure-for-damaged-nails-long-lasting-photos-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eacrylic%20or%20gel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20especially%20along%20the%20cuticle%20area%2C%20which%20is%20more%20prone%20to%20lifting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221fd33c4b-bce3-45d5-b6ea-5d1b744ac593%5C%22%3EAvoid%20creating%20air%20bubbles%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223744%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20close-up%20of%20fingernails%20as%20someone%20uses%20a%20wooden%20cuticle%20stick%20to%20push%20back%20their%20cuticles.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68518fe285e81483682c3eb4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222808%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPrepping%20the%20cuticles%20can%20prevent%20air%20bubbles%20from%20forming.%3Cp%3EMikhailPopov%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20proper%20preparation%2C%20air%20bubbles%20may%20form%20between%20the%20natural%20and%20fake%20nails.%20After%20a%20few%20hand%20washes%2C%20water%20can%20get%20into%20the%20gaps%2C%20loosen%20the%20glue%2C%20and%20cause%20lifting%20of%20the%20nail%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tokyonailschicago.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETokyo%20Nails%3C%2Fa%3E%20co-owner%20Nomundari%20Uuganbayar%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20avoid%20this%20issue%2C%20she%20suggests%20a%20solid%20prep%20process%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbad-nail-habits-ruining-your-nails-2018-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epushing%20your%20cuticles%20back%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20cleaning%20the%20area.%20She%20also%20recommends%20buffing%20the%20natural%20nails%20to%20create%20a%20soft%20texture%2C%20and%20making%20sure%20they're%20dry%20before%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2285a7ccb1-f1bc-4285-8cba-3756be68ad44%5C%22%3ERemember%20that%20glue%20is%20a%20trial-and-error%20process%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20close-up%20of%20hands%20as%20the%20left%20hand%20presses%20a%20fake%20nail%20onto%20the%20right%20hand's%20natural%20nail%2C%20which%20has%20nail%20glue%20applied.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F685196bc85e81483682c3f5c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222730%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EApply%20glue%20to%20both%20the%20natural%20nail%20and%20the%20press-on.%3Cp%3EKseniia%20Barlit%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20there's%20no%20exact%20measurement%20for%20the%20perfect%20amount%20of%20glue%2C%20Kandalec%20told%20BI%20it's%20best%20to%20fill%20the%20well%20of%20the%20press-on%20nail.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20glue%20seeps%20out%20from%20the%20sides%20of%20the%20fake%20nail%2C%20you've%20likely%20added%20too%20much.%20In%20that%20case%2C%20you%20can%20use%20a%20wooden%20cuticle%20stick%20to%20clean%20up%20the%20excess.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBe%20sure%20to%20apply%20glue%20to%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fno-manicure-natural-nail-trend-popular-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enatural%20nail%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20well%20before%20placing%20the%20press-on.%20If%20you're%20able%2C%20Kandalec%20suggests%20fitting%20the%20press-on%20closely%20to%20your%20cuticles%20so%20it%20sits%20just%20beneath%20the%20skin%20along%20the%20sides%20of%20your%20nail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f5aea7d0-136d-47f8-a363-d7205b5e45dc%5C%22%3EApply%20the%20press-on%20at%20an%20angle%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fsweetbobanails%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETeresa%20%26quot%3BTere%26quot%3B%20Rodriguez%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Chicago-based%20artist%20and%20licensed%20nail%20tech%20who%20offers%20a%20press-on%20nail%20subscription%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20best%20to%20apply%20the%20fake%20nail%20at%20an%20angle%20for%20about%2020%20to%2025%20seconds%20to%20allow%20the%20glue%20to%20set.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERodriguez%20recommends%20applying%20the%20press-on%20nail%20from%20the%20cuticle%2C%20then%20pushing%20down%20toward%20the%20top%20for%20an%20effective%20grip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f47ba941-ec93-4304-bdd3-c8ee4bbc261d%5C%22%3EAvoid%20water%20for%20about%2020%20minutes%20after%20application%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20best%20to%20avoid%20getting%20your%20nails%20wet%20for%20at%20least%2020%20minutes%20after%20the%20application.%20This%20is%20because%20the%20glue%20needs%20time%20to%20fully%20dry%20and%20bond%20the%20press-on%20to%20your%20natural%20nail.%20Washing%20your%20hands%20too%20soon%20can%20cause%20the%20bond%20to%20weaken%20and%20lead%20to%20premature%20lifting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Rodriguez%2C%20a%20good%20set%20of%20press-on%20nails%20can%20last%20up%20to%20two%20or%20three%20weeks%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-you-should-never-do-after-getting-manicure-nail-artists%5C%22%20target%3D%5