6quot%3Bregular%26quot%3B%20doctors%20typically%20don't%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-elite-athletes-curb-water-intake-after-4pm-top-dietitian-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eelectrolyte%3C%2Fa%3E%20levels%20as%20well%20as%20the%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bheavy%20metals%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20lead%2C%20mercury%20%E2%80%94%20potentially%20poisonous%20substances%20that%20can%20sometimes%20lurk%20in%20our%20air%2C%20water%2C%20and%20food.%20It%20might%20even%20find%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wanted%20to%20see%20what%20all%20the%20big%20buzz%20was%20about%20with%20this%20%24500%20annual%20blood-and-pee%20testing%20service%2C%20so%20I%20tried%20it%20out.%20Disclaimer%3A%20I%20didn't%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20it%2C%20because%20Function%20Health%20gave%20out%20free%20trials%20to%20journalists%20as%20the%20company%20is%20still%20in%20beta%20testing%20mode.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20my%20Function%20results%20led%20me%20to%20seek%20out%20more%20advice%20from%20doctors%20than%20I%20usually%20would%2C%20to%20help%20me%20separate%20the%20signal%20from%20the%20noise%20in%20all%20the%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226dc5fe0a-902f-43cc-b07f-efdc842f9024%5C%22%3EI%20freaked%20out%20about%20all%20the%20little%20cholesterol%20particles%20hiding%20out%20in%20my%20blood%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221624%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22doctor%20holding%20heart%20model%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6865975f85e81483682d458f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMy%20Function%20results%20flagged%20seven%20%26quot%3Bout%20of%20range%26quot%3B%20tests%2C%20and%20three%20of%20those%20were%20related%20to%20heart%20health.%3Cp%3EChinnapong%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%20is%20that%20Function%20is%20not%20a%20huge%20time%20suck.%20It%20takes%20about%2015%20minutes%20to%20get%20the%20initial%20testing%20done%20and%20you%20can%20roll%20up%20to%20just%20about%20any%20Quest%20Diagnostics%20lab%20location%20nationwide%20(except%20in%20Hawaii%20and%20Rhode%20Island).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20tests%20measure%20over%2090%20different%20biomarkers%20in%20your%20blood%20and%20urine%2C%20including%20almost%20all%20the%20typical%20stuff%20you'd%20find%20in%20a%20doctor's%20office%20(except%20STD%20testing).%20Function%20performed%20roughly%20three%20times%20the%20number%20of%20tests%20I%20had%20done%20the%20last%20time%20I%20went%20to%20the%20doctor's%20office%20for%20routine%20bloodwork.%20There%20were%20more%20measurements%20related%20to%20hormones%2C%20key%20nutrients%2C%20my%20metabolism%2C%20and%20heart%20health.%20Function%20Health%20also%20measured%20my%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-the-maximum-age-of-humans-115-or-older-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebiological%20age%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20scientifically%20squishy%20indicator%20of%20health%20and%20fitness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20so%20many%20tests%20being%20run%2C%20there's%20a%20good%20chance%20that%20something%20you%20measure%20when%20you%20do%20Function%20will%20come%20back%20abnormal.%20That%20doesn't%20always%20mean%20there's%20something%20wrong%20with%20you%3B%20sometimes%20your%20own%20%26quot%3Bnormal%26quot%3B%20doesn't%20fit%20neatly%20into%20a%20given%20reference%20range.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFunction%20is%20OK%20with%20having%20a%20few%20errant%20flags%20in%20the%20data%2C%20and%20encourages%20re-testing%20any%20out%20of%20range%20labs.%20Their%20ethos%20is%20the%20more%20information%2C%20the%20better.%20It's%20about%20creating%20a%20more%20detailed%20picture%20of%20your%20overall%20health%2C%20not%20making%20sure%20each%20test%20is%20perfect%20every%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20are%20%26quot%3Bwanting%20to%20know%20more%20about%20their%20biology%2C%20and%20to%20be%20advocates%20for%20their%20own%20health%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Mar