3C%2Fa%3E%20profile%20has%20probably%20found%20themselves%20asking%20questions%20like%20these.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20asked%20LinkedIn%20experts%20for%20their%20tips%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-job-recruiter-reached-out-linkedin-profile-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eoptimizing%20your%20LinkedIn%20profile%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20building%20your%20professional%20brand%20on%20the%20site.%20The%20next%20time%20you%20need%20to%20brush%20up%20on%20your%20profile%20(hint%3A%20you're%20probably%20not%20doing%20it%20enough)%2C%20here%20are%20their%20do's%20and%20don'ts%20for%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-linkedin-got-weird-work-life-blurred-lines-of-oversharing-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20networking%20site%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223c2b5f38-4916-40df-926e-8534e6785763%5C%22%3EOptimizing%20your%20profile%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn%20gives%20you%20the%20option%20to%20default%20to%20your%20current%20job%20title%20in%20your%20headline.%20But%20%26quot%3Bhaving%20skills%20in%20the%20headline%20is%20one%20of%20the%20areas%20that%20can%20really%20help%20you%20show%20up%20more%20prominently%20in%20search%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20executive%2C%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%2C%20and%20LinkedIn%20writer%20Virginia%20Franco.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsider%20putting%20two%20or%20three%20of%20the%20top%20keywords%20or%20skills%20associated%20with%20your%20job%20target%20in%20your%20headline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThink%20of%20it%20as%20your%20220-character%20elevator%20pitch%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Beth%20Granger%2C%20a%20consultant%20who%20focuses%20on%20networking%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-improve-your-linkedin-profile-networking-and-content-strategy-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebuilding%20your%20professional%20brand%20on%20LinkedIn%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20along%20with%20hard%20skills%2C%20you%20also%20want%20to%20%26quot%3Bbalance%20those%20keywords%20with%20a%20feel%20for%20your%20personality%2C%20to%20generate%20chemistry%20for%20you%20as%20a%20candidate%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Meg%20Guiseppi%2C%20executive%20job%20search%20strategist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20neglect%20their%20banners%2C%20but%20they're%20%26quot%3Byour%20own%20professional%20billboard%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Granger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFranco%20has%20seen%20clients%20take%20the%20three%20top%20keywords%20affiliated%20with%20their%20job%20target%2C%20add%20their%20name%2C%20and%20use%20that%20as%20their%20background%20image.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20your%20About%20section%2C%20strike%20a%20more%20conversational%20tone%20than%20you%20would%20in%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%20(That%20means%20ditching%20the%20third-person%20voice.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20real%20chance%20to%20tell%20the%20reader%20about%20the%20problems%20that%20you%20fix%2C%20maybe%20some%20details%20about%20your%20leadership%20style%2C%20or%20what%20makes%20you%20tick%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Franco.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20lead%20with%20what%20you%20most%20want%20someone%20to%20know%2C%20since%20they%20may%20not%20click%20to%20read%20to%20the%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Experience%20section%2C%20Franco%20focuses%20on%20the%20last%2015%20years%20of%20her%20work%20history.%20List%20your%20job%20responsibilities%2C%20not%20just%20your%20employer%20and%20job%20title%2C%20and%20don't%20just%20copy-paste%20from%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%20You%20can%20describe%20a%20specific%20project%20and%20its%20results%2C%20or%20go%20more%20in-depth%20than%20you%20could%20in%20a%20bulleted%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHighlight%20for%20each%20role%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20you%20were%20brought%20on%20to%20do%2C%20what%20things%20looked%20like%20at%20the%20end%2C%20and%20high-level%20how%20you%20went%20about%20doing%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Franco%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChoose%20from%20one%20of%20the%20pre-populated%20job%20title%20choices