y%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20brother%20got%20everything.%E2%80%9D%20Before%201956%2C%20women%20in%20Hindu%20families%20were%20not%20legal%20heirs%20to%20joint%20family%20property.%20That%20meant%20land%2C%20ancestral%20homes%2C%20and%20farmland%20%E2%80%94%20all%20went%20to%20the%20sons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%201956%20law%20made%20daughters%20legal%20heirs%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20But%20even%20then%2C%20the%20right%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20equal%2C%20especially%20if%20the%20father%20was%20still%20alive.%20It%20was%20only%20with%20the%202005%20amendment%20that%20the%20law%20went%20further%2C%20declaring%20daughters%20as%20coparceners%20%E2%80%94%20equal%20in%20rights%20and%20duties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20plain%20terms%3A%20if%20your%20brother%20gets%20land%2C%20you%20get%20land.%20No%20questions.%20No%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E5.%20The%20Dissolution%20of%20Muslim%20Marriages%20Act%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%3A%201939%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%3A%20British%20India%20(for%20Muslims)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20one%20is%20often%20overlooked%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20quietly%20one%20of%20the%20most%20empowering.%20It%20gave%20Muslim%20women%20the%20right%20to%20legally%20divorce%20their%20husbands%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20was%20historically%20much%20easier%20for%20men%20via%20talaq.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20listed%20specific%20grounds%3A%20cruelty%2C%20impotence%2C%20desertion%2C%20non-payment%20of%20maintenance%2C%20and%20even%20failure%20to%20perform%20marital%20obligations.%20This%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20about%20ending%20marriage%20lightly%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20about%20giving%20women%20the%20legal%20tools%20to%20walk%20away%20from%20abuse%20or%20neglect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuplo